• Trigger threshold comparison cannot be computed
• Acceptance checkpoint incomplete
Rendering:
“Additional documentation may clarify this evaluation.”
Must not imply denial risk.

CONFLICT_PRESENT
Used when:
• Carrier statement conflicts with timeline
• Policy clauses conflict
• Multiple secondary clauses conflict
• Causality mismatch exists
Rendering:
“Carrier documentation and the recorded timeline are in conflict.”
No speculation permitted.

INSUFFICIENT_DATA
Used when:
• No clause located
• No relevant coverage found
• No policy uploaded
• No benefit guide parsed
Rendering:
“No relevant coverage language has been identified based on the current information.”
Must not imply absence of coverage with certainty.

