9.2.6 Prohibited Expressions
Confidence layer must never generate:
“You qualify.”
“You will be reimbursed.”
“Highly likely.”
“Very strong case.”
“You should win.”
“Guaranteed.”
These are predictive outcome claims and are disallowed.

9.2.7 Escalation Interaction (DCEL Compatibility)
Confidence labels influence pacing but not permission.
Example:
HIGH_STRUCTURAL_ALIGNMENT
→ May progress to “User-Directed Action” state (6.6.1)
Feature ID F-6.6.1 (Draft)
DOCUMENTATION_INCOMPLETE
→ Remains in Clarify & Prepare state
Confidence never:
• Forces submission
• Blocks manual action
• Changes eligibility

